# 🔴 Investigation 1 — Open Redirection

## What is Open Redirection?

An Open Redirect vulnerability occurs when a web application uses unvalidated user input to redirect users to external URLs. Attackers exploit this to send victims from a trusted domain to a malicious one — commonly used in phishing campaigns.

**Example of a malicious redirect:**
```
https://victim.com/post?postId=https://attacker.com
```
The victim sees `victim.com` in the link but gets sent to `attacker.com`.

