# 🛠️ Tools & Commands Reference

| Tool | What it Does |
|------|-------------|
| `cat` | Display the full log file |
| `grep -E` | Filter lines using regex patterns |
| `awk '{print $1}'` | Extract the IP address field |
| `awk -F'"' '{print $6}'` | Extract the user agent field |
| `awk '{print $9}'` | Extract the HTTP status code field |
| `sort` | Sort results alphabetically or numerically |
| `uniq -c` | Count and deduplicate repeated lines |
| `sort -rn` | Sort by count, highest first |
| `head -5` | Show only the first 5 results |

